==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Macedonian]] '''[[Македонија]]''' (''Makedonia'') "highland", from '''[[македнос]]''' (''makednos''), "high, tall", from [[Ancient]] Macedonian '''[[макос]]''' (''makos''), "height, length"; in [[Ionic Macedonia]]: '''[[мекос]]''' (''mekos''). In ancient Macedonian mythology, '''[[Македонија]]''' (''Makedonia'') was named after '''[[Македон]]''' (''Makedon''), the [[patriarch]] of the Macedonians.

